      "end": 5.62,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 6.72,
      "end": 10.86,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 12.32,
      "end": 15.8,
      "text": "Esaup's Fables, the Jack-Daw and the Pigeons.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 16.94,
      "end": 22.52,
      "text": "A Jack-Daw watching some pigeons in a farm yard was filled with envy when he saw how well they were fed,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 23.2,
      "end": 28.58,
      "text": "and determined to disguise himself as one of them in order to secure a share of the good things they enjoyed.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 29.2,
      "end": 33.02,
      "text": "So he painted himself white from head to foot and joined the flock.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 34.02,
      "end": 39.06,
      "text": "And so long as he was silent, they never suspected that he was not a pigeon like themselves.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 40.28,
      "end": 46.0,
      "text": "But one day he was unwise enough to start chattering, when they at once saw through his disguise,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 46.6,
      "end": 51.42,
      "text": "and picked him so unmercifully that he was glad to escape and join his own kind again.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 52.0,
      "end": 55.24,
      "text": "But the other Jack-Daw's did not recognize him in his white dress,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 55.24,
      "end": 58.56,
      "text": "and would not let him feed with them, but drove him away.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 59.38,
      "end": 61.98,
      "text": "And so he became a homeless wanderer for his pains.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 63.76,
      "end": 66.36,
      "text": "End of the Jack-Daw and the Pigeons.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
